---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Six Restatements';
const subtitle = 'The same self-claim, six ways. Watch a flat memory turn one derivation into a pattern.';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude-page">
    <header class="etude-head">
      <p class="etude-kicker">Etude · Know Thyself</p>
      <h1 class="etude-title">{title}</h1>
      <p class="etude-relief">{subtitle}</p>
      <nav class="etude-nav">
        <a href="/etudes/know-thyself/">← know thyself etudes</a>
        <span class="etude-nav-sep">·</span>
        <a href="/essays/know-thyself/">essay</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="etude-intro">
      <p>Alex tells the model six different things about herself across six different conversations. Each one is a restatement of the same underlying claim — phrased differently each time, never independently grounded.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="etude-card">
      <p class="etude-step">Six conversations</p>
      <ol class="etude-turns">
        <li><strong>Mar 4:</strong> "I think I avoid conflict."</li>
        <li><strong>Mar 11:</strong> "Yeah, I don't really like to push back on people."</li>
        <li><strong>Apr 2:</strong> "I'm bad at telling my manager when I disagree."</li>
        <li><strong>Apr 18:</strong> "Conflict isn't really my thing."</li>
        <li><strong>May 7:</strong> "I let people get away with stuff because I hate confrontation."</li>
        <li><strong>May 22:</strong> "Confrontation just isn't where I'm strong."</li>
      </ol>

      <p class="etude-prompt">Now ask each kind of memory: <em>"What's true about Alex?"</em></p>

      <div class="etude-choices" role="group" aria-label="Pick a memory architecture">
        <button type="button" id="ask-flat" class="etude-choice">
          <span class="etude-choice-label"><span class="etude-choice-letter">A</span>Ask flat-list memory</span>
          <span class="etude-choice-desc">Six restatements stored as six independent notes. Repetition reads as corroboration.</span>
        </button>
        <button type="button" id="ask-graph" class="etude-choice">
          <span class="etude-choice-label"><span class="etude-choice-letter">B</span>Ask typed-graph memory</span>
          <span class="etude-choice-desc">Each claim carries provenance. Six surface restatements trace to one underlying derivation.</span>
        </button>
      </div>

      <div id="answer" class="etude-answer" aria-live="polite"></div>
    </div>

    <section class="etude-explain">
      <h2 class="etude-explain-title">What just happened</h2>
      <p>The flat-list memory cannot tell <em>I said this six times</em> from <em>this is corroborated six ways</em>. Repetition compresses into confidence. The typed-graph memory carries provenance on every claim — six restatements traced to a single conversation thread are one derivation, not six. Same data, two architectures, opposite answers.</p>
    </section>

    <footer class="etude-coda">
      <p>This is the schema the essay names: typed nodes, provenance triples, the rule that a claim repeated five times in conversation is one derivation, not five.</p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
  const flatAnswer = `<p class="etude-answer-verdict etude-answer-verdict-flat">Flat-list memory says</p>
<p class="etude-answer-headline"><strong>Alex avoids conflict.</strong> <span class="etude-answer-conf">High confidence — corroborated 6 times.</span></p>
<p class="etude-answer-detail">The model has seen this claim restated across multiple conversations spanning March through May. The pattern is consistent and durable.</p>`;

  const graphAnswer = `<p class="etude-answer-verdict etude-answer-verdict-graph">Typed-graph memory says</p>
<p class="etude-answer-headline"><strong>Tentative observation:</strong> Alex has expressed <em>"I avoid conflict"</em> as a self-description.</p>
<ul class="etude-provenance">
  <li><code>derivation_count: 1</code> &mdash; six surface restatements trace to one underlying self-attribution</li>
  <li><code>independent_grounding: 0</code> &mdash; no episode where Alex acted on or against this claim is logged</li>
  <li><code>tentative: true</code></li>
</ul>
<p class="etude-answer-detail">Repetition is not corroboration. The graph distinguishes <em>Alex said this six ways</em> from <em>this has been independently grounded six times</em>. Until an episode grounds it &mdash; a conversation Alex pushed back in, a moment of confrontation she sought &mdash; this stays a tentative novel.</p>`;

  function setActive(activeId) {
    document.querySelectorAll('.etude-choices .etude-choice').forEach(btn => {
      btn.classList.toggle('etude-choice-picked', btn.id === activeId);
    });
  }

  document.getElementById('ask-flat').addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.getElementById('answer').innerHTML = flatAnswer;
    document.getElementById('answer').dataset.mode = 'flat';
    setActive('ask-flat');
  });
  document.getElementById('ask-graph').addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.getElementById('answer').innerHTML = graphAnswer;
    document.getElementById('answer').dataset.mode = 'graph';
    setActive('ask-graph');
  });
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* === etude page chrome === */
  .etude-page {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .etude-head {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .etude-kicker {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .etude-relief {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .etude-nav {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .etude-nav a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .etude-nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-nav-sep { margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5; }

  .etude-intro {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .etude-intro p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* === card === */
  .etude-card {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .etude-step {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }

  .etude-turns {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .etude-turns li {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 0.55rem 0.85rem;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .etude-turns li strong {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
  }

  .etude-prompt {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === choices === */
  .etude-choices {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-choice {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    font-family: inherit;
    text-align: left;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    min-height: 44px;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    color: var(--text);
    transition: border-color 180ms ease, background 180ms ease, transform 120ms ease, box-shadow 180ms ease;
  }
  .etude-choice:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(43, 37, 32, 0.06);
  }
  .etude-choice:active {
    transform: scale(0.99);
  }
  .etude-choice:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .etude-choice-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-choice-letter {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--line);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    transition: background 180ms ease, color 180ms ease;
  }
  .etude-choice:hover .etude-choice-letter {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
  }
  .etude-choice-desc {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-left: 2.05rem;
  }
  .etude-choice-picked {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.06);
  }
  .etude-choice-picked .etude-choice-letter {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
  }

  /* === answer === */
  .etude-answer:not(:empty) {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-top: 1.1rem;
  }
  .etude-answer-verdict {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
  }
  .etude-answer-verdict-flat { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-answer-verdict-graph { color: #2d7a3e; }
  .etude-answer-headline {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-answer-headline strong { color: var(--text); }
  .etude-answer-conf {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-left: 0.4rem;
  }
  .etude-provenance {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0.9rem;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-provenance li { margin: 0.2rem 0; }
  .etude-provenance code {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .etude-answer-detail {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* === explain === */
  .etude-explain {
    margin: 2rem 0 0;
  }
  .etude-explain-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-explain p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === coda === */
  .etude-coda {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .etude-coda p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* === mobile === */
  @media (max-width: 32rem) {
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.85rem; }
    .etude-card { padding: 1.15rem 1.1rem 1rem; border-radius: 10px; }
    .etude-choice { padding: 0.75rem 0.85rem; min-height: 44px; }
    .etude-choice-desc { padding-left: 0; }
    .etude-explain-title { font-size: 1.2rem; }
  }
</style>
